{"tid":2076233,"cid":10,"subCid":0,"title":"Neil Druckmann 對於The Last of Us 2劇情轉折採訪","createTime":"2020-06-23T11:03:57.000Z","updateTime":"2020-06-24T09:19:57.000Z","uid":176282,"like":3,"dislike":31,"uniUserReply":43,"replies":[{"pid":"05ff200cffde3f6c45c85db18a82332c64720f6a","tid":2076233,"uid":176282,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-06-23T11:03:57.000Z","msg":"全文地址： <a href=\"https://www.indiewire.com/2020/06/the-last-of-us-part-ii-interview-neil-druckmann-halley-gross-spoilers-1234568597/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiewire.com%2F2020%2F06%2Fthe-last-of-us-part-ii-interview-neil-druckmann-halley-gross-spoilers-1234568597%2F&d=91nyg34XrGq4aGOua7i4JdmOP5%2FvN4RyP%2Fy1e26q30o%3D&h=724360b1\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.indiewire.com/2020/06/the-last-of-us-part-ii-interview-neil-druckmann-halley-gross-spoilers-1234568597/</a><br />\n<br />\n以下係我覺得非常有趣嘅一段，TLOU2點解大家代入唔到角色？因爲我Neil Cuckman特登咁做㗎，哈哈哈<br />\n記者：These games are famous for how they engage with the player&rsquo;s agency and sense of control. In &ldquo;The Last of Us,&rdquo; our alignment with Joel compels us to justify his actions as he murders innocent people to protect Ellie. In &ldquo;Part II,&rdquo; it feels as if the characters are trying to wrest control back from us. We fight Ellie, but Abby makes the decision to walk away. We fight Abby, but Ellie chooses to spare her life.<br />\n<br />\nDruckmann: I think the ending of &ldquo;The Last of Us&rdquo; worked for a lot of people because of how in the beginning of the game we did a lot to put you in alignment with Joel, and to make you care for Ellie, and because we delayed Joel making the choice to take care of Ellie for a while &mdash; people like Tess keep making that choice for him. We knew that some people were not going to be on board with Joel&rsquo;s decision at the end of the game, but we tried to make it so that even if you&rsquo;re not in alignment with him by the time you got there, we&rsquo;ve hinted at what he&rsquo;s capable of so much that you&rsquo;re still on board for the ride. There&rsquo;s something interesting that happens when you&rsquo;re not in alignment with the character and the game makes you do something that you don&rsquo;t want to do &mdash; you wrestle with those decisions in a different way than you would be able to in a passive medium."},{"pid":"6c57f5b7d08de9c374b8e74d702ac98975bf81a7","tid":2076233,"uid":176282,"like":0,"dislike":23,"score":-23,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-23T11:15:48.000Z","msg":"另一段關於阿祖之死，原本設定係臨死前會嗌Sarah，原來佢當Ellie係condom咋，就算同Ellie出生入死咁多年，佢心入面都係得自己親生女。所以大家明Ellie點解咁憎祖未？都唔係親生老竇<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\n記者：And she gets there just in the nick of time. She travels all the way to Santa Barbara just to let Abby live &mdash; to save her life, even. Abby&rsquo;s decision to heed Lev&rsquo;s caution and spare Ellie is similarly abrupt but understandable. Were you nervous about selling those key moments? <br />\n<br />\nDruckmann: There are so many emotional parts of the game that for a long time didn&rsquo;t land, and every time it&rsquo;s so daunting to make them work. So often it&rsquo;s just the iterative process of creation and cutting out a bunch of stuff that we realized wasn&rsquo;t necessary. What comes to mind right now is Joel&rsquo;s death. In the first edit of that scene, you felt nothing. Ellie&rsquo;s being held down and Joel&rsquo;s looking at her and we had this idea of like, &ldquo;Oh man Joel&rsquo;s brain is so fucked up at that moment that the only word that&rsquo;s coming out of his mouth is his daughter&rsquo;s name, &lsquo;Sarah.'&rdquo; It felt powerful, but then Troy [Baker] &mdash; to his credit &mdash; was like, &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t think he should say anything.&rdquo; We shot both versions, and Troy was right. The scene was stronger without it."},{"pid":"1fbba80db2a77d9cdd8ca6a71950469cd4da3cad","tid":2076233,"uid":92680,"like":35,"dislike":0,"score":35,"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2020-06-23T12:03:04.000Z","msg":"仲以為係一流嘅生還者一定會避到高爾夫球棍"},{"pid":"f100ddc94c6f97d2407a540b41e9c564521a4d62","tid":2076233,"uid":52228,"like":52,"dislike":1,"score":51,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-23T12:07:04.000Z","msg":"仆佢個街<br />\n佢根本以撚玩家為樂<br />\n以後有佢嘅名嘅遊戲就一定唔會買"},{"pid":"4afd8282125a92ce5dcb92e5f9d745f8b95b6716","tid":2076233,"uid":66669,"like":26,"dislike":0,"score":26,"quote":{"pid":"f100ddc94c6f97d2407a540b41e9c564521a4d62","tid":2076233,"uid":52228,"like":52,"dislike":1,"score":51,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-23T12:07:04.000Z","msg":"仆佢個街<br />\n佢根本以撚玩家為樂<br />\n以後有佢嘅名嘅遊戲就一定唔會買"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-23T12:27:57.000Z","msg":"佢同Hailey Gross兩條粉皮仲係度圍爐打J話你愈憎隻遊戲愈憎佢兩個，佢地就愈爽<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"d9df0632df85f403fb3a314f6534c93246794888","tid":2076233,"uid":52228,"like":10,"dislike":0,"score":10,"quote":{"pid":"4afd8282125a92ce5dcb92e5f9d745f8b95b6716","tid":2076233,"uid":66669,"like":26,"dislike":0,"score":26,"quote":{"pid":"f100ddc94c6f97d2407a540b41e9c564521a4d62","tid":2076233,"uid":52228,"like":52,"dislike":1,"score":51,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-23T12:07:04.000Z","msg":"仆佢個街<br />\n佢根本以撚玩家為樂<br />\n以後有佢嘅名嘅遊戲就一定唔會買"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-23T12:27:57.000Z","msg":"佢同Hailey Gross兩條粉皮仲係度圍爐打J話你愈憎隻遊戲愈憎佢兩個，佢地就愈爽<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-23T12:30:24.000Z","msg":"我覺得係因為根本佢哋對TLOU1個劇本冇乜感覺<br />\n真係打機嘅有幾多SJW<br />\n諗住All in SJW Naughty Dog 以後橋住對手都有錢賺嘅<br />\n下世啦"},{"pid":"8ff7d43cae84d7edd9699cc02ac4f8a45aabae86","tid":2076233,"uid":12994,"like":17,"dislike":0,"score":17,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-23T12:33:25.000Z","msg":"今次咁樣做臭朵 睇怕都幾難落台<br />\n最好就全撚部人剪碟 退款<br />\n咁就好睇<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"